  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Cancer Clinical Status Assessment - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_clinical_status_assessment">Cancer Clinical Status Assessment</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_clinical_status_assessment">Cancer Clinical Status Assessment</xref>
 is the assessment of a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s clinical condition.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_clinical_status_assessment">Cancer Clinical Status Assessment</xref>
 may take place at a review point within the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_care_plan">Cancer Care Plan</xref>
 or may be required if the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s condition changes during treatment, for example if the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 reports toxicity as a result of treatment.        </p>
  </div>
